# Bandsintown artist API key (obtained via Bandsintown for Artists →
# Settings → General → Get API Key). Used ONLY at build time by
# web/src/lib/bandsintown.ts to fetch upcoming concerts and bake them into
# the static HTML.
#
# IMPORTANT: This variable MUST NOT be VITE_-prefixed. A VITE_ prefix would
# inline the value into the shipped client JS bundle, leaking the key to the
# browser (D-09). It is read as process.env.BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID during the
# build (locally, and as a build-scope env var on Vercel).
BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID=

# --- Vercel deploy notes (moved here from vercel.json; Vercel's config schema
# rejects any unknown key including "$comment", so these can't live in that file) ---
# - Project Root Directory MUST be set to "web" in the dashboard
#   (Settings -> General -> Root Directory) for web/vercel.json to take effect
#   (RESEARCH.md Pitfall 5).
# - With Root Directory=web, Vercel auto-detects the Vite framework preset and,
#   because the repo root has npm workspaces + a committed root lockfile,
#   auto-installs from the monorepo root (no custom installCommand needed). Keep
#   "Include source files outside of the Root Directory in the Build Step" enabled.
# - Add BANDSINTOWN_APP_ID as a Production + Preview env var scoped to Build only,
#   WITHOUT a VITE_ prefix (D-09).
# - Every workspace package.json must keep a unique `name` for Vercel's
#   skip-unaffected-builds detection (enforced by web/src/test/prerender-output.test.ts).
